>>>	tutorial_prologue			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	none
	narrator		Now you'll have to choose three things you like. Each LIKE is tied to one or several Romance Options.
	narrator		Your LIKES will "soft lock" you into some ROs you'll encounter more often.
	narrator		You can correct this "soft lock" by meeting other ROs in the FOOD COURT, which you'll see later.
	narrator		After the LIKES phase, you'd be asked to choose a top 3 within a category. You'll choose your first, second, and third-favorite option, in descending order.
	narrator		This will shape your starting STATS.

>>>	prologue_1			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>layout	none
	narrator		Ah, Spooky Con... for some, it was just a nerdy convention; but for us?
	narrator		It was four days to celebrate our many passions and obsessions fiercely; unapologetically.
	narrator		And we weren't alone: regardless of what you loved, you could always find people who'd make you feel seen and understood.
	narrator		Anywhere else, we might've been seen as weirdos and misfits...
	narrator		...but here we could finally feel like, no matter who we were, we belonged.

>>>	prologue_2			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>layout	none
	narrator		But as dreamy as Spooky Con was, it also came with its own set of pressures, some of which we already knew so well...
	narrator		At the end of those four days, the afterparty loomed over our heads, posing that one evergreen question:	
	narrator		Would we get a date for that night?
	narrator		As uncertainty plagued our hearts, we couldn't help but think of the six hottest nerds at the con...

