>>>	prologue_2_end
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>layout	none
	narrator		It had to be one of them, but who?
	narrator		We had four days to gather some courage and shoot our shot.
	narrator		What was the worst that could happen? Being rejected and alone the rest of our lives? Ha!
	narrator		We'd had our fair share of love and rejection... this surely wasn't our first rodeo.
	narrator		And as we had grown to know ourselves better, we realized we felt more confident.

>>>	prologue_3			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>layout	none
	narrator		We weren't new to all this, so this time we challenged ourselves with a goal other than finding love.
	narrator		With the support of Zoe and Liam, we had decided to take on a project we had been putting off for too long...

>>>	prologue_3b
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>layout	none
	narrator		Making our own comic!
	narrator		We had so many ideas, and yet we always found excuses not to work on them.
	narrator		But the con was the perfect setting to find inspiration and go for it.

>>>	prologue_4
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>layout	none
	narrator		The fear of failure had stopped us for too long; but then we reminded ourselves of the one thing that always kept us going:
	narrator		That we were young and unafraid...
	narrator		...and we were ready to start.
